00:18:32,758 --> 00:18:35,420
My God, she dropped the groceries all over.

263
00:18:40,065 --> 00:18:42,192
Look at this.

264
00:18:42,301 --> 00:18:44,360
Let's clean it up. Come on.

265
00:18:46,238 --> 00:18:49,833
There must be something.
Chemotherapy, something?

266
00:18:49,909 --> 00:18:53,276
Take this. Nothing works.
It's the same thing Jim had.

267
00:18:53,345 --> 00:18:55,540
There's nothing they can do.

268
00:18:57,550 --> 00:19:01,384
I need you to be strong for me.
I'm counting on you. Come on.

269
00:19:03,989 --> 00:19:05,115
Amalia.

270
00:19:05,825 --> 00:19:08,453
- We knew this day was coming.
- No, not today.

271
00:19:08,794 --> 00:19:10,489
Please, not today.

272
00:19:10,629 --> 00:19:12,824
- I'm in shock.
- We all are.

273
00:19:13,866 --> 00:19:16,494
- Shouldn't somebody tell Brandon?
- No.

274
00:19:16,602 --> 00:19:18,593
Nick's got enough problems.

275
00:19:19,605 --> 00:19:20,765
Excuse me.

276
00:19:22,975 --> 00:19:24,465
Yes, he called.

277
00:19:24,944 --> 00:19:26,138
Get here as...

278
00:19:26,212 --> 00:19:29,409
Fifteen minutes would be great.
That's the other line.

279
00:19:30,783 --> 00:19:33,115
What is this huge oatmeal for?

280
00:19:33,352 --> 00:19:34,979
Who's gonna eat this?

281
00:19:35,754 --> 00:19:38,120
And you got two, just to be sure?

282
00:19:38,724 --> 00:19:39,884
Nick.

283
00:19:40,359 --> 00:19:41,951
There's a limousine outside.

284
00:19:42,027 --> 00:19:44,461
It's the Harts. Don't worry about that.

285
00:19:44,997 --> 00:19:47,761
Bill, how are you? Good to see you.

286
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:50,898
- Sara.
- We heard on the way to the airport.

287
00:19:51,504 --> 00:19:54,871
- That house. I wish I was going with you.
- So do we.

288
00:19:55,908 --> 00:20:00,038
Since you're the first people here,
you'll know everybody who's here.

289
00:20:01,547 --> 00:20:03,640
- Are you feeding this dog?
- Of course.

290
00:20:03,716 --> 00:20:06,947
I know you want to keep it small and cute.
This is my mother.

291
00:20:07,319 --> 00:20:08,650
Anybody home?

292
00:20:09,822 --> 00:20:13,087
Mrs. Bingham and son.
So glad you could make it.

293
00:20:14,393 --> 00:20:16,759
- Oh, you.
- You don't look sick.

294
00:20:16,829 --> 00:20:18,626
- Missed you.
- You do.

295
00:20:18,697 --> 00:20:20,062
- How you doing?
- Hi.

296
00:20:20,132 --> 00:20:22,293
Come on. Let's meet everybody.

297
00:20:22,501 --> 00:20:23,593
Okay.

298
00:20:23,969 --> 00:20:26,403
Nick, how about Matt in New York?

299
00:20:26,572 --> 00:20:29,632
Definitely. Lina, Andrew. Bill, Sara.

300
00:20:30,175 --> 00:20:32,541
To put everyone's mind at ease...

301
00:20:32,611 --> 00:20:35,808
I've transferred all my accounts to Amalia.

302
00:20:35,881 --> 00:20:38,008
But I've got some bad news.

303
00:20:40,119 --> 00:20:42,087
There's no money in them.

304
00:20:42,254 --> 00:20:44,313
Why give your mother such a hard time?

305
00:20:44,390 --> 00:20:46,381
You must be tough on kids these days.

306
00:20:46,458 --> 00:20:48,119
I'm just teasing, Ma.

307
00:20:49,562 --> 00:20:51,894
This is my party.

308
00:20:52,431 --> 00:20:53,523
So...

309
00:20:54,366 --> 00:20:56,891
there'll be no wake and no funeral.

310
00:20:57,036 --> 00:20:59,800
So grab the free booze while it lasts.
Come on.

311
00:20:59,905 --> 00:21:02,135
- Uncle Nick?
- What's with the hair?

312
00:21:02,207 --> 00:21:03,731
It's for a show.

313
00:21:03,809 --> 00:21:07,301
- You're a dancer now.
- Yeah, and Dad's not doing leaps.

314
00:21:08,781 --> 00:21:10,578
I thought he'd be in bed...

315
00:21:10,716 --> 00:21:12,980
not joking and pouring champagne.

316
00:21:13,285 --> 00:21:14,513
Amalia.

317
00:21:15,487 --> 00:21:17,614
- Where's Brandon?
- Who cares?

318
00:21:18,290 --> 00:21:20,815
- Nick hasn't told Brandon?
- Nick couldn't handle it.

319
00:21:20,893 --> 00:21:22,884
You lost so much weight.

320
00:21:23,162 --> 00:21:26,097
I thought your ass was Jodie Foster's chin.

321
00:21:26,165 --> 00:21:29,965
Babe, you know me,
I never miss an opening...

322
00:21:30,936 --> 00:21:32,164
or a closing.

323
00:21:32,237 --> 00:21:33,534
You look fantastic.

324
00:21:33,606 --> 00:21:35,972
This a tan, or Ava Gardner's
Show Boat make-up?

325
00:21:36,041 --> 00:21:38,168
"I always look well when I'm near death."

326
00:21:38,243 --> 00:21:41,212
Greta Garbo in Camille.
And we move on to Double Jeopardy.

327
00:21:41,647 --> 00:21:44,115
What is this? The Big Chill, or what?

328
00:21:44,183 --> 00:21:46,014
More like The Deep Freeze.

329
00:21:46,752 --> 00:21:48,686
I want an unbiased opinion.

330
00:21:49,321 --> 00:21:50,379
You.

331
00:21:51,557 --> 00:21:53,457
Which of us is tanner?

332
00:21:54,994 --> 00:21:58,760
Yes. Monty,
have you met my mother, Amalia?

333
00:22:03,736 --> 00:22:06,398
Wanted to see if you're paying attention.

334
00:22:07,706 --> 00:22:09,799
I'm going to fix the music.

335
00:22:10,843 --> 00:22:12,606
Why don't we sing Christmas carols?

336
00:22:12,678 --> 00:22:15,943
What do they sing in Australia?
"We Three Kangaroos"?

337
00:22:16,015 --> 00:22:17,277
Oh, man.

338
00:22:20,552 --> 00:22:21,814
Quincy.

339
00:22:24,957 --> 00:22:27,391
Don't mind the car. Sit. Speak.

340
00:22:31,130 --> 00:22:33,496
I'm sorry. We're very busy right now.

341
00:22:33,799 --> 00:22:36,563
Don't you have a paper route or something?

342
00:22:37,836 --> 00:22:39,064
Brandon.

343
00:22:39,705 --> 00:22:41,002
Charlene.

344
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,840
It's been a while. What are you doing here?

345
00:22:43,909 --> 00:22:47,572
I tried calling you. Nick's sick.
He's having a gathering.

346
00:22:48,714 --> 00:22:51,444
We're heading out of town this afternoon.

347
00:22:51,517 --> 00:22:53,144
And he doesn't want me there.

348
00:22:53,218 --> 00:22:55,550
Brandon, it's a farewell party.

349
00:22:56,121 --> 00:22:57,554
They did a brain scan.

350
00:22:57,623 --> 00:23:00,990
He has a few days before
his mind's completely gone.

351
00:23:01,060 --> 00:23:02,288
No.

352
00:23:03,062 --> 00:23:05,496
Why does this have to happen now?

353
00:23:05,864 --> 00:23:09,163
Of course, he planned this whole thing
to annoy you.

354
00:23:11,603 --> 00:23:13,230
Maybe I can fly back.

355
00:23:13,305 --> 00:23:15,705
There won't be time. Do what you want.

356
00:23:20,546 --> 00:23:21,911
What's going on?

357
00:23:22,281 --> 00:23:24,715
- I'm going over to Nick's house.
- For what?

358
00:23:24,783 --> 00:23:25,909
He's very sick.

359
00:23:25,984 --> 00:23:28,953
Again? Who'll finish directing the scene?

360
00:23:29,021 --> 00:23:31,785
Who cares?
It's not directing, it's animal training.

361
00:23:31,857 --> 00:23:33,222
Stan, take over, will you?

362
00:23:43,936 --> 00:23:45,426
When will you do it?

363
00:23:45,504 --> 00:23:47,096
This Friday night.

364
00:23:47,172 --> 00:23:50,903
Not gonna end up like Jim and Jack,
unable to take care of myself.

365
00:23:51,477 --> 00:23:53,172
You'll still be alive.

366
00:23:53,245 --> 00:23:54,769
You call this living?

367
00:23:55,180 --> 00:23:56,704
I'm too weak to work.

368
00:23:56,915 --> 00:23:58,712
The pain is unbearable.

369
00:23:58,851 --> 00:24:01,183
Look at me. I'm ready.

370
00:24:02,121 --> 00:24:04,089
Sounds like a good idea to me.

371
00:24:04,923 --> 00:24:07,983
- Some champagne, dear?
- Sounds simply marvelous.

372
00:24:08,794 --> 00:24:10,455
Here goes my diet.

373
00:24:12,030 --> 00:24:13,054
Hi, Brandon.

374
00:24:13,932 --> 00:24:16,366
- My best piece, so far.
- She's beautiful.

375
00:24:16,435 --> 00:24:17,424
That's Liz.

376
00:24:17,503 --> 00:24:18,527
Happy birthday.

377
00:24:18,604 --> 00:24:21,471
Joe wants us here Saturday
to arrange his body.

378
00:24:22,174 --> 00:24:23,232
Arrange?

379
00:24:23,342 --> 00:24:26,311
Tony says the Seconals
can cause convulsions.

380
00:24:27,312 --> 00:24:30,873
I wouldn't want my family to find me
wearing these crepes.

381
00:24:34,386 --> 00:24:36,251
I'll miss you, Joey.

382
00:24:37,055 --> 00:24:38,249
That's nice of you, darling.

383
00:24:42,561 --> 00:24:45,394
This might not be a pretty picture.
You know that?

384
00:24:46,198 --> 00:24:48,189
Come on, Nick, that's enough.

385
00:24:50,402 --> 00:24:52,962
- You sure you can handle this?
- Yes.

386
00:25:39,885 --> 00:25:41,944
Oh, no. What do we do?

387
00:25:44,389 --> 00:25:45,549
The pillow.

388
00:25:45,624 --> 00:25:46,852
Are you nuts?

389
00:25:47,960 --> 00:25:51,828
Can you imagine waking up after this?
He could be a vegetable.

390
00:25:59,671 --> 00:26:00,899
Oh, God.

391
00:26:01,673 --> 00:26:05,507
I read in The Final Exit
you should use a plastic bag. I'll get one.

392
00:26:05,577 --> 00:26:07,067
What's Final Exit?

393
00:26:07,212 --> 00:26:08,372
It's a book.

394
00:26:08,847 --> 00:26:11,907
You wouldn't know it,
because no one's filmed it.

395
00:26:12,584 --> 00:26:13,915
I found one.

396
00:26:21,026 --> 00:26:22,459
Much better.

397
00:26:26,798 --> 00:26:29,164
Juan, hi. Look, we...

398
00:26:29,234 --> 00:26:31,828
- He's still alive.
- No, he's not. No.

399
00:26:31,937 --> 00:26:35,839
Give him time. The pills haven't taken effect.
Come on. Call Tony.

400
00:26:36,308 --> 00:26:37,900
Calm down, Juan. Come on.

401
00:26:54,192 --> 00:26:55,420
Is he gone?

402
00:26:56,962 --> 00:26:58,122
Yeah.

403
00:27:08,840 --> 00:27:10,330
Who's got a camera?

404
00:27:14,046 --> 00:27:15,138
Joe.

405
00:27:16,815 --> 00:27:18,009
Anybody home?

406
00:27:21,219 --> 00:27:23,380
Elvis has left the building.

407
00:27:24,456 --> 00:27:25,616
Come on.

408
00:27:28,727 --> 00:27:29,751
I'm going to miss Joe.

409
00:27:38,770 --> 00:27:39,998
Is this a girl?

410
00:27:40,072 --> 00:27:42,802
- Yes.
- So I'm not the only bitch in the room.

411
00:27:56,722 --> 00:27:57,984
Nikko.

412
00:27:58,357 --> 00:28:00,018
Nikko, we're here.

413
00:28:03,628 --> 00:28:05,493
Baby sister.

414
00:28:07,299 --> 00:28:10,393
You only call if it's a matter of life or death.

415
00:28:10,469 --> 00:28:12,164
- I always call you.
- Do not.

416
00:28:12,237 --> 00:28:13,431
Do, too.

417
00:28:14,006 --> 00:28:16,497
Thanks for coming, doll face.

418
00:28:17,609 --> 00:28:19,133
Hi, Aunt Fanny.

419
00:28:19,778 --> 00:28:21,541
You still tailgating semis?

420
00:28:21,613 --> 00:28:24,138
They kept losing us, trying to change lanes.

421
00:28:24,683 --> 00:28:25,877
Not easy.

422
00:28:26,718 --> 00:28:29,278
- We have to go.
- I thought the plane waited for you.

423
00:28:29,354 --> 00:28:31,686
Yeah, but we'll lose our take-off spot.

424
00:28:31,957 --> 00:28:33,686
We'll be thinking of you.

425
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:35,824
Bill.

426
00:28:35,894 --> 00:28:37,691
- Goodbye, Nick.
- Take care.

427
00:28:39,064 --> 00:28:40,361
Goodbye, Nick.

428
00:28:40,732 --> 00:28:41,790
You know...

429
00:28:41,867 --> 00:28:44,927
I love Sara and Bill, but that dog...

430
00:28:45,003 --> 00:28:46,732
Come on, let's go inside.

431
00:28:53,712 --> 00:28:55,145
You made it.

432
00:28:56,081 --> 00:28:57,708
Can't stay long.

433
00:29:06,558 --> 00:29:07,820
Hello, Amalia.

434
00:29:21,606 --> 00:29:25,269
- I think dementia is setting in.
- What is the Snow Queen doing here?

435
00:29:38,523 --> 00:29:39,888
What a surprise.

436
00:29:41,026 --> 00:29:42,425
Charlene told me.

437
00:29:44,229 --> 00:29:46,197
You look great.

438
00:29:46,598 --> 00:29:49,829
Live fast, die young,
leave a good-looking corpse.

439
00:29:52,104 --> 00:29:53,469
How's Opala?

440
00:29:54,306 --> 00:29:55,398
Fine.

441
00:29:57,008 --> 00:29:59,442
I was just heading to the airport.

442
00:29:59,878 --> 00:30:03,541
And where are we whisking off to
this holiday season?

443
00:30:04,082 --> 00:30:07,483
Australia.
We're shooting the rest of the film there.

444
00:30:07,652 --> 00:30:09,051
You and Junior?

445
00:30:12,757 --> 00:30:16,591
You called this morning.
I thought you might want to see me.

446
00:30:16,995 --> 00:30:19,930
He's seen you, and it's not a pretty picture.

447
00:30:23,068 --> 00:30:24,660
When's your plane?

448
00:30:25,871 --> 00:30:26,997
Soon.

449
00:30:27,706 --> 00:30:31,039
We were going to say goodbye
to the boys at the firehouse.

450
00:30:35,647 --> 00:30:38,639
- You got nerve showing up here.
- Get used to me.

451
00:30:38,717 --> 00:30:41,117
Why don't you say goodbye and go?

452
00:30:45,023 --> 00:30:46,957
I'll go when I'm good and ready.

453
00:30:47,225 --> 00:30:49,591
You know how to do that so well.

454
00:30:50,295 --> 00:30:54,732
- Don't make me run at this wake.
- Let's get a drink or two, or six.

455
00:30:55,500 --> 00:30:56,990
Are you okay, hon?

456
00:30:58,370 --> 00:31:01,771
"He has every characteristic of a dog,
except loyalty."

457
00:31:04,776 --> 00:31:07,040
Henry Fonda in The Best Man.

458
00:31:07,846 --> 00:31:09,313
Vodka rocks.

459
00:31:10,815 --> 00:31:12,544
He looks better than ever.

460
00:31:12,684 --> 00:31:14,777
He's got four, maybe five days.

461
00:31:15,253 --> 00:31:18,222
I always figured there'd be time
to talk things through.

462
00:31:18,290 --> 00:31:20,258
Uncle Brandon,
I thought you weren't coming.

463
00:31:20,325 --> 00:31:22,190
God, you look so tall.

464
00:31:23,929 --> 00:31:26,227
Tony, make him leave.

465
00:31:26,398 --> 00:31:29,458
He's upsetting Nick,
and my mother's nervous enough.

466
00:31:29,534 --> 00:31:31,627
- It's okay. I'll handle it.
- Okay?

467
00:31:31,703 --> 00:31:35,298
- Is your father coming?
- He called. He'll be here any minute.

468
00:31:36,208 --> 00:31:38,039
Will you excuse us?

469
00:31:41,513 --> 00:31:44,038
Nick's family needs to say goodbye
in the time left.

470
00:31:44,115 --> 00:31:45,707
What'll happen to him?

471
00:31:45,917 --> 00:31:49,353
- You don't want to know.
- What will happen to him?

472
00:31:50,422 --> 00:31:53,084
It's Progressive Multifocal
Leukoencephalopathy.

473
00:31:53,158 --> 00:31:56,184
It moves fast.
He's already losing his peripheral vision.

474
00:31:56,328 --> 00:31:58,319
And you're here to help?

475
00:31:59,231 --> 00:32:00,596
Brandon...

476
00:32:01,600 --> 00:32:05,536
your being here, it's just adding
a lot of stress and confusion.

477
00:32:05,604 --> 00:32:08,095
Do us a favor.
Catch your plane before he gets back.

478
00:32:08,173 --> 00:32:09,299
I've a right to be here.

479
00:32:09,374 --> 00:32:10,500
You lost that right...

480
00:32:10,575 --> 00:32:12,805
- when you kicked him out.
- Who are you to judge?

481
00:32:12,877 --> 00:32:14,902
- This is between me and Nick.
- What's this?

482
00:32:18,750 --> 00:32:21,310
Looks like one of Nick's art pieces.

483
00:32:26,825 --> 00:32:27,814
My God.

484
00:32:29,160 --> 00:32:31,890
It's our friends who have died of AIDS.

485
00:32:32,897 --> 00:32:34,888
There's so many of them.

486
00:32:38,870 --> 00:32:40,394
Jim Bixby was first.

487
00:32:40,472 --> 00:32:42,599
He and Carl were together for...

488
00:32:42,674 --> 00:32:45,074
- How did you stay together for so long?
- Wasn't easy.

489
00:32:45,143 --> 00:32:47,270
Two male egos aren't easy to mesh.

490
00:32:47,512 --> 00:32:49,241
He died in the hospital...

491
00:32:49,314 --> 00:32:51,282
tubes coming out of everywhere.

492
00:32:51,349 --> 00:32:53,078
You're a doctor, right?

493
00:32:53,151 --> 00:32:57,019
Ran the AIDS Unit at County
until I couldn't take it anymore.

494
00:32:57,222 --> 00:32:58,382
Now I teach.

495
00:32:58,523 --> 00:33:00,320
There's different types of AIDS?

496
00:33:00,759 --> 00:33:01,748
No.

497
00:33:03,295 --> 00:33:05,559
Different infections
attack a weak immune system.

498
00:33:05,630 --> 00:33:07,723
With Jack, it was toxoplasmosis.

499
00:33:08,366 --> 00:33:10,459
He decided to die at home.

500
00:33:16,241 --> 00:33:18,436
- Can we go outside?
- No, I'm staying here.

501
00:33:18,510 --> 00:33:20,341
And Joey had skin lesions.

502
00:33:20,412 --> 00:33:23,540
He took pills,
but he didn't get the dosage right.

503
00:33:23,782 --> 00:33:25,613
Jeez, what happened?

504
00:33:27,085 --> 00:33:28,814
He needed some help.

505
00:33:29,888 --> 00:33:30,912
You?

506
00:33:30,989 --> 00:33:33,321
I entered medicine to help people.

507
00:33:33,391 --> 00:33:34,653
How soon?

508
00:33:35,927 --> 00:33:38,555
Please, just don't make this any harder.

509
00:33:38,630 --> 00:33:42,293
- I'm not leaving till I talk to him.
- He needs his tranquility.

510
00:33:43,868 --> 00:33:46,701
Houdini's licking his balls, and Jim says:

511
00:33:46,771 --> 00:33:49,968
"I wish I could do that."
I said, "Better pet him first."

512
00:33:50,041 --> 00:33:52,032
So much for tranquility.

513
00:33:56,281 --> 00:33:58,613
I thought you had Australia to go to.

514
00:33:58,683 --> 00:34:01,516
- Can we go somewhere to talk?
- Go ahead, talk.

515
00:34:03,555 --> 00:34:04,817
What's the plan?

516
00:34:04,889 --> 00:34:08,586
Everything's taken care of.
Someone will show you the storyboards.

517
00:34:08,660 --> 00:34:09,786
How soon?

518
00:34:09,861 --> 00:34:12,694
- It was going to be tonight.
- Tonight?

519
00:34:12,764 --> 00:34:15,324
But some friends are coming tomorrow.

520
00:34:15,400 --> 00:34:18,767
I wanted to wait,
