stop being mad at you, Nick.

1028
01:02:29,394 --> 01:02:30,520
At me?

1029
01:02:33,031 --> 01:02:36,797
You kicked me out,
and you left me to die alone...

1030
01:02:37,169 --> 01:02:40,627
away from the home I built,
even away from my dog.

1031
01:02:41,039 --> 01:02:43,599
Don't be a prick. I didn't dump you.

1032
01:02:43,976 --> 01:02:45,807
It was a shock for me, too.

1033
01:02:45,877 --> 01:02:47,572
I needed time to adjust.

1034
01:02:47,646 --> 01:02:49,477
And you really tried.

1035
01:02:49,915 --> 01:02:51,109
I did.

1036
01:02:51,583 --> 01:02:55,075
We stopped making love,
but I stayed with you.

1037
01:02:56,855 --> 01:03:00,154
I think you were jealous of me,
for not being sick.

1038
01:03:00,459 --> 01:03:02,620
You were jealous
of anyone who came near me.

1039
01:03:02,694 --> 01:03:04,127
I wasn't jealous.

1040
01:03:04,196 --> 01:03:06,562
You're Greek, you can't help it.

1041
01:03:06,832 --> 01:03:08,197
I'm dying.

1042
01:03:08,567 --> 01:03:10,899
Why should I care what you say?

1043
01:03:12,537 --> 01:03:14,368
You pushed me away...

1044
01:03:16,408 --> 01:03:19,605
because you were afraid
that I would abandon you.

1045
01:03:21,847 --> 01:03:23,872
I wouldn't have left you.

1046
01:03:26,385 --> 01:03:29,013
We'll never really know now, will we?

1047
01:03:30,789 --> 01:03:32,552
Do you want me...

1048
01:03:32,624 --> 01:03:35,320
to cancel my flight
and come back tomorrow?

1049
01:03:35,394 --> 01:03:36,520
What?

1050
01:03:37,229 --> 01:03:38,890
Do what you want.

1051
01:03:39,564 --> 01:03:41,828
You'll either be here, or not.

1052
01:03:42,634 --> 01:03:44,067
Like always.

1053
01:03:53,445 --> 01:03:54,673
No.

1054
01:03:54,946 --> 01:03:56,436
What's wrong?

1055
01:03:57,549 --> 01:03:58,777
Nothing.

1056
01:04:02,120 --> 01:04:04,588
You're going to love going to court.

1057
01:04:04,656 --> 01:04:09,116
I am not walking off into the sunset,
leaving my mother empty-handed.

1058
01:04:23,208 --> 01:04:24,937
I guess this is it.

1059
01:04:26,311 --> 01:04:27,801
I can't do it.

1060
01:04:29,281 --> 01:04:30,771
I can't leave.

1061
01:04:36,521 --> 01:04:38,182
It's for the best.

1062
01:04:41,727 --> 01:04:44,287
We tried to make it work, but we just...

1063
01:04:44,363 --> 01:04:45,853
We just can't.

1064
01:04:48,333 --> 01:04:49,925
This is my home.

1065
01:04:57,442 --> 01:05:00,036
Your new place will become your home.

1066
01:05:02,647 --> 01:05:04,774
Can I come back here to die?

1067
01:07:51,516 --> 01:07:53,313
Good morning, Amalia.

1068
01:07:57,522 --> 01:07:59,114
What's all this?

1069
01:08:03,128 --> 01:08:06,757
You used to say,
"I don't believe in that religious crap."

1070
01:08:10,802 --> 01:08:12,292
Couldn't hurt.

1071
01:08:25,951 --> 01:08:28,181
You know what you ought to do?

1072
01:08:29,187 --> 01:08:32,679
You ought to go back to making
that kind of jewelry you used to make.

1073
01:08:32,757 --> 01:08:34,384
God, it was good.

1074
01:08:39,631 --> 01:08:42,122
Remember not to look down all the time.

1075
01:08:42,200 --> 01:08:44,191
Keep your eyes up. Okay?

1076
01:08:45,470 --> 01:08:46,562
Okay?

1077
01:08:47,906 --> 01:08:49,965
Nikko, please don't leave me.

1078
01:08:50,041 --> 01:08:52,168
I can't make it without you.

1079
01:08:56,514 --> 01:08:58,482
You're going to have to.

1080
01:09:08,893 --> 01:09:11,828
Do I smell hot onion bagels,
or did you sleep in that shirt?

1081
01:09:11,896 --> 01:09:14,262
Yes, it's me, Monty. I'm at Nick's house.

1082
01:09:14,332 --> 01:09:17,324
I want you to bring me a fresh shirt
and a new tongue.

1083
01:09:18,470 --> 01:09:21,132
No, just come over as soon as you can.

1084
01:09:24,109 --> 01:09:27,476
You look pretty hung-over
for someone who doesn't drink.

1085
01:09:27,545 --> 01:09:30,241
I'm having little problems with my vision.

1086
01:09:30,315 --> 01:09:33,011
Pieces are missing, like blank spots.

1087
01:09:33,084 --> 01:09:35,075
You give me some of that?

1088
01:09:35,387 --> 01:09:36,786
Who are you?

1089
01:09:37,555 --> 01:09:39,045
You're my dad.

1090
01:09:42,427 --> 01:09:46,090
This is richness worth a second cup,
Charlene. How do you do it?

1091
01:09:46,164 --> 01:09:49,224
Nick never asked for a second cup
of my coffee.

1092
01:09:50,635 --> 01:09:52,296
How are you doing?

1093
01:10:01,446 --> 01:10:02,970
Come on, Opala.

1094
01:10:05,383 --> 01:10:07,374
Lina and I almost made it once.

1095
01:10:07,452 --> 01:10:08,544
What?

1096
01:10:09,154 --> 01:10:11,679
We had this electric moment
when you said to me:

1097
01:10:11,756 --> 01:10:13,849
"Why'd you have to be gay?"

1098
01:10:14,426 --> 01:10:15,415
I said to you:

1099
01:10:15,493 --> 01:10:17,757
"Me? Why do you have to be a woman?"

1100
01:10:20,131 --> 01:10:21,996
Here's some Thai food.

1101
01:10:22,400 --> 01:10:25,130
You can always use more with this crowd.

1102
01:10:26,137 --> 01:10:27,661
You're staying?

1103
01:10:28,206 --> 01:10:29,298
Yeah.

1104
01:10:29,674 --> 01:10:31,665
He always loved this dog.

1105
01:10:32,811 --> 01:10:34,802
He's out in the back yard.

1106
01:10:34,879 --> 01:10:36,073
Thanks.

1107
01:10:38,416 --> 01:10:41,783
I had an electric moment with her.
She's not a woman.

1108
01:10:45,190 --> 01:10:46,555
Who's that?

1109
01:10:47,459 --> 01:10:49,893
- Brandon.
- Oh, God, he's back.

1110
01:10:50,028 --> 01:10:51,290
And Opala.

1111
01:10:51,362 --> 01:10:52,989
Come on, Houdini.

1112
01:10:53,665 --> 01:10:55,690
Opala. You met Houdini, haven't you?

1113
01:10:55,767 --> 01:10:57,234
Sure she has.

1114
01:10:57,302 --> 01:10:58,326
Hi.

1115
01:10:58,570 --> 01:11:00,037
You showed up.

1116
01:11:00,105 --> 01:11:03,199
- How do you like my brand new shoes?
- Nice.

1117
01:11:03,475 --> 01:11:06,069
They were expensive, too. I thought...

1118
01:11:07,011 --> 01:11:08,103
I should use them.

1119
01:11:08,179 --> 01:11:10,374
What kind of a name is Opala?

1120
01:11:10,448 --> 01:11:12,245
"Opala" means "trash" in Hawaiian.

1121
01:11:12,317 --> 01:11:15,411
They found her in a garbage bag
by the roadside.

1122
01:11:15,587 --> 01:11:17,384
- For you.
- Thanks.

1123
01:11:17,522 --> 01:11:19,285
Don't you miss them?

1124
01:11:19,724 --> 01:11:21,248
I miss a lot of things.

1125
01:11:21,326 --> 01:11:24,921
When Opala was a puppy,
she used to sleep in between them.

1126
01:11:24,996 --> 01:11:26,395
Lucky bitch.

1127
01:11:27,298 --> 01:11:29,664
I got this for you a while back.

1128
01:11:34,672 --> 01:11:36,264
A sundial watch?

1129
01:11:38,977 --> 01:11:41,241
So is this out of one of your catalogs?

1130
01:11:41,312 --> 01:11:42,973
What do you think?

1131
01:11:43,748 --> 01:11:46,273
This'll come in handy
for the next seven hours.

1132
01:11:46,351 --> 01:11:48,182
- Nick, listen...
- Nick.

1133
01:11:49,053 --> 01:11:50,179
Matt.

1134
01:11:50,488 --> 01:11:53,889
How are you, man? Good to see you.
Thanks for coming.

1135
01:11:54,325 --> 01:11:56,520
- For you.
- That's a pathetic poinsettia.

1136
01:11:56,594 --> 01:11:59,028
Babe, welcome to Christmas in LA...

1137
01:11:59,097 --> 01:12:01,565
where Santa has sweat stains.

1138
01:12:01,633 --> 01:12:03,157
How's New York?

1139
01:12:03,735 --> 01:12:05,600
- Brandon's here?
- Sure.

1140
01:12:06,004 --> 01:12:09,235
You want to see the finishing touches
at the site?

1141
01:12:14,412 --> 01:12:17,040
You mean, the latest house he designed.

1142
01:12:17,115 --> 01:12:18,412
I'd love to see it.

1143
01:12:18,483 --> 01:12:19,882
Could we go?

1144
01:12:21,319 --> 01:12:23,412
Wait now, we can't take a whole group.

1145
01:12:23,488 --> 01:12:24,887
Can I come?

1146
01:12:25,824 --> 01:12:27,155
If you want.

1147
01:12:27,225 --> 01:12:29,125
Why don't I take you some other time?

1148
01:12:29,194 --> 01:12:30,661
- Oh, sure.
- Let's go.

1149
01:12:30,728 --> 01:12:33,060
This needs water. You take this.

1150
01:12:33,398 --> 01:12:35,832
- I'll be back.
- Should I do the kitchen?

1151
01:12:36,434 --> 01:12:40,200
- I guess we didn't make the A-list.
- For this I flew five hours?

1152
01:12:40,271 --> 01:12:41,932
Let's get a drink.

1153
01:12:42,140 --> 01:12:45,769
Does my hair look like one of the seagulls
from the Exxon Valdez oil spill?

1154
01:12:45,844 --> 01:12:47,436
I meant to tell you that.

1155
01:12:50,014 --> 01:12:52,505
Nick, we've done some great work together.

1156
01:12:52,584 --> 01:12:54,449
It ain't over for you.

1157
01:12:54,552 --> 01:12:57,749
I get to walk away,
but you gotta keep on slaving.

1158
01:13:00,158 --> 01:13:02,183
I've always been amazed...

1159
01:13:03,361 --> 01:13:05,386
at the way you see things.

1160
01:13:05,964 --> 01:13:08,865
Does the client know
I'm checking out today?

1161
01:13:09,000 --> 01:13:10,024
No.

1162
01:13:10,235 --> 01:13:12,533
When he finds out I've kicked...

1163
01:13:12,604 --> 01:13:16,233
you should jack up the price
based on the sympathy factor.

1164
01:13:19,911 --> 01:13:21,242
Here we are.

1165
01:13:22,447 --> 01:13:25,143
They're finishing up the kitchen today.

1166
01:13:35,827 --> 01:13:37,055
Come on.

1167
01:13:42,000 --> 01:13:43,729
I'll be right back.

1168
01:13:47,138 --> 01:13:48,935
This is unbelievable.

1169
01:13:50,742 --> 01:13:52,937
This reminds me of Santorini.

1170
01:13:53,011 --> 01:13:54,535
Do you like it?

1171
01:13:54,812 --> 01:13:55,904
Yeah.

1172
01:13:56,080 --> 01:13:57,240
So...

1173
01:13:57,515 --> 01:14:00,746
- you and Tony aren't living together?
- No, we're just friends.

1174
01:14:00,818 --> 01:14:02,251
For a while now.

1175
01:14:02,320 --> 01:14:03,878
What about you?

1176
01:14:04,055 --> 01:14:05,386
You were...

1177
01:14:05,456 --> 01:14:07,754
very perceptive about Zack.

1178
01:14:12,330 --> 01:14:15,458
I was just thinking about
that trip to Lake Tahoe.

1179
01:14:16,067 --> 01:14:17,329
Remember?

1180
01:14:18,403 --> 01:14:20,633
You were teaching me how to ski.

1181
01:14:20,705 --> 01:14:23,435
I was giving you such a hard time.

1182
01:14:26,344 --> 01:14:29,006
You were so patient with me.

1183
01:14:31,916 --> 01:14:35,352
You remember when I finally got it...

1184
01:14:36,621 --> 01:14:39,590
and we skied down the hill together...

1185
01:14:40,925 --> 01:14:42,119
just...

1186
01:14:42,727 --> 01:14:45,093
swirling through the powder...

1187
01:14:46,464 --> 01:14:48,329
laughing and shouting?

1188
01:14:51,803 --> 01:14:53,930
Nobody connects like we did.

1189
01:14:58,042 --> 01:15:00,476
Switch gyms, you'll find somebody.

1190
01:15:00,578 --> 01:15:02,478
Stop it, Nick. Stop it.

1191
01:15:02,814 --> 01:15:04,839
We're running out of time.

1192
01:15:05,650 --> 01:15:07,379
It's not my fault.

1193
01:15:09,153 --> 01:15:10,916
We better get going.

1194
01:15:11,422 --> 01:15:14,357
They'll be pissed at me for taking him away.

1195
01:15:27,705 --> 01:15:28,967
Hi, honey.

1196
01:15:29,040 --> 01:15:31,440
Brandon, you've met my wife, Pat.

1197
01:15:33,378 --> 01:15:35,209
My favorite cousin.

1198
01:15:36,347 --> 01:15:37,678
Excuse me.

1199
01:15:37,915 --> 01:15:40,475
What's the idea of leaving the party
without telling me?

1200
01:15:40,551 --> 01:15:43,281
So sorry, Mommy. I'll never do it again.

1201
01:15:43,688 --> 01:15:45,155
Don't wander.

1202
01:15:47,458 --> 01:15:49,119
Awake at the wake.

1203
01:15:49,227 --> 01:15:51,821
You're wearing the same thing
you had on yesterday?

1204
01:15:51,896 --> 01:15:53,124
I stayed.

1205
01:15:53,197 --> 01:15:55,392
Holding a torch on the porch.

1206
01:15:56,534 --> 01:15:58,900
Didn't you spend the night with Alex?

1207
01:15:58,970 --> 01:16:01,063
Feeling vibrant near his hydrant.

1208
01:16:01,139 --> 01:16:03,334
Didn't you think he was cute?

1209
01:16:04,208 --> 01:16:06,574
- You two aren't really serious?
- Hardly.

1210
01:16:06,644 --> 01:16:08,339
- How's Nick?
- Doing okay.

1211
01:16:08,413 --> 01:16:10,904
- Are you holding up?
- I'm glad to see you.

1212
01:16:10,982 --> 01:16:13,473
- Who are all these people?
- Nick's friends.

1213
01:16:13,551 --> 01:16:15,678
I've never seen them before.

1214
01:16:15,920 --> 01:16:17,751
I want you to get them to go.

1215
01:16:17,822 --> 01:16:19,881
- He invited...
- Every single one of them.

1216
01:16:19,957 --> 01:16:21,925
- I'll see what I can do.
- Don't see.

1217
01:16:21,993 --> 01:16:25,793
Get them the hell out of this house.
My son is going to die.

1218
01:16:26,064 --> 01:16:28,259
I want to have time with him.

1219
01:16:32,203 --> 01:16:33,261
Yes.

1220
01:16:34,272 --> 01:16:35,637
Roast beef.

1221
01:16:38,109 --> 01:16:40,304
Got to have an empty stomach.

1222
01:16:42,313 --> 01:16:43,940
An empty stomach?

1223
01:16:44,849 --> 01:16:46,339
For the pills.

1224
01:17:10,775 --> 01:17:12,970
Was the spanakopita that bad?

1225
01:17:15,646 --> 01:17:16,977
The sun...

1226
01:17:17,548 --> 01:17:19,175
keeps going down.

1227
01:17:20,284 --> 01:17:23,185
I can't believe this is his last afternoon.

1228
01:17:24,288 --> 01:17:25,687
How'd it go?

1229
01:17:28,126 --> 01:17:31,357
I can't get through to him.
I don't know if it's...

1230
01:17:31,429 --> 01:17:33,624
the sickness or the drugs...

1231
01:17:33,998 --> 01:17:36,091
No, it's just him.

1232
01:17:37,468 --> 01:17:38,867
Keep trying.

1233
01:17:40,605 --> 01:17:42,072
We have to spread the word.

1234
01:17:42,507 --> 01:17:45,601
Nick's family wants everyone
to leave by sunset.

1235
01:17:51,215 --> 01:17:53,206
We're all supposed to go?

1236
01:17:59,590 --> 01:18:02,957
It's my party, and I'll die if I want to

1237
01:18:03,027 --> 01:18:04,858
Die if I want to

1238
01:18:04,929 --> 01:18:06,920
Die if I want to

1239
01:18:07,098 --> 01:18:11,125
You would die, too, if it happened to you

1240
01:18:14,038 --> 01:18:16,131
Lighten up, please.

1241
01:18:16,207 --> 01:18:17,936
It's not a funeral...

1242
01:18:18,442 --> 01:18:19,500
yet.

1243
01:18:19,977 --> 01:18:22,844
- I want a picture.
- Good, Aunt Fanny, here we go.

1244
01:18:23,548 --> 01:18:26,642
All right. Here, Nick. Come on.
Look at me. Smile.

1245
01:18:29,387 --> 01:18:31,287
I want an 8 x 10.

1246
01:18:31,422 --> 01:18:33,083
Everyone, out of the kitchen.

1247
01:18:33,157 --> 01:18:35,648
Let me see your face, Nick.
Here we go. Great.

1248
01:18:37,595 --> 01:18:40,120
- One with Matt.
- Matt, sit down.

1249
01:18:43,167 --> 01:18:45,067
Squeeze together, guys.

1250
01:18:45,203 --> 01:18:48,400
Would you like to have a picture taken
with Nikko?

1251
01:18:49,240 --> 01:18:52,641
No, thank you.
I have one at home that I really love.

1252
01:18:53,077 --> 01:18:54,339
Let's go.

1253
01:19:01,519 --> 01:19:03,384
Everybody, get together. Get tight.

1254
01:19:03,454 --> 01:19:05,081
Wait, wait, wait.

1255
01:19:11,462 --> 01:19:13,054
That'll be nice.

1256
01:19:13,164 --> 01:19:15,462
Where's Dad? Dad, get in there.

1257
01:19:17,168 --> 01:19:19,193
All right, squeeze together.

1258
01:19:20,438 --> 01:19:21,962
I hope these come out.

1259
01:19:22,039 --> 01:19:23,506
Pretty, okay.

1260
01:19:23,808 --> 01:19:25,503
One more, one more.

1261
01:19:25,576 --> 01:19:27,737
No, I'll go over here.

1262
01:19:30,982 --> 01:19:32,973
Yeah, good. Look this way.

1263
01:19:33,050 --> 01:19:34,813
And smile.

1264
01:19:35,653 --> 01:19:37,848
Now, just me and the children.

1265
01:19:46,030 --> 01:19:49,466
Pretty. That's a good one.
Mom, all right, one with you.

1266
01:19:52,403 --> 01:19:54,394
I do hope these come out.

1267
01:19:56,874 --> 01:19:59,206
Nick's taken his father's place.

1268
01:19:59,677 --> 01:20:02,669
Greek sons
always watch out for their mothers.

1269
01:20:03,080 --> 01:20:05,173
How about one with Brandon?

1270
01:20:05,316 --> 01:20:07,807
Sure. Brandon, come, get in there.

1271
01:20:13,624 --> 01:20:16,422
All right. Good, guys. Great.

1272
01:20:21,265 --> 01:20:23,859
- That'll be nice to have.
- Who's next?

1273
01:20:24,802 --> 01:20:26,599
Do one with us and the baby.

1274
01:20:26,671 --> 01:20:28,696
I was thinking about that.

1275
01:20:29,407 --> 01:20:33,468
Don't forget. You have to help me
get everybody out before sunset.

1276
01:20:41,285 --> 01:20:43,082
That's great, thanks.

1277
01:21:00,271 --> 01:21:02,466
Can we go someplace and talk?

1278
01:21:06,844 --> 01:21:09,369
Why didn't you tell me you had AIDS?

1279
01:21:11,782 --> 01:21:13,807
'Cause I knew you'd be ashamed.

1280
01:21:13,884 --> 01:21:17,718
How do you think I feel, being left out?
Facing it all now?

1281
01:21:17,788 --> 01:21:21,315
You've been ashamed of me
ever since you found out I was gay.

1282
01:21:23,627 --> 01:21:25,720
I've always had a lot of prejudices.

1283
01:21:25,796 --> 01:21:26,854
No shit.

1284
01:21:26,931 --> 01:21:28,831
I thought a lot about this.

1285
01:21:28,899 --> 01:21:30,526
When I dated your mother...

1286
01:21:30,601 --> 01:21:33,035
her family rejected me,
because I was Jewish.

1287
01:21:33,104 --> 01:21:35,231
I know exactly how you feel.

1288
01:21:35,673 --> 01:21:37,265
I'm sure you do.

1289
01:21:40,578 --> 01:21:44,878
Watching you with your friends
has made me see things differently.

1290
01:21:47,118 --> 01:21:49,245
They care about you so much.

1291
01:22:00,131 --> 01:22:03,066
I'm sorry I wasn't a good father to you.

1292
01:22:09,507 --> 01:22:12,237
You were a good father when I was a kid.

1293
01:22:12,676 --> 01:22:16,578
You gave me my first watercolor set
that got me interested in art.

1294
01:22:16,647 --> 01:22:17,807
I did?

1295
01:22:17,882 --> 01:22:21,079
It was a deluxe set. It had 42 colors.

1296
01:22:21,852 --> 01:22:24,480
I did my first paintings with it, Dad.

1297
01:22:26,924 --> 01:22:29,688
I'm so proud
of how you're handling yourself.

1298
01:22:37,568 --> 01:22:38,694
Excuse me.

1299
01:22:40,604 --> 01:22:43,869
Your family is at our house,
driving me crazy. I can't do it anymore.

1300
01:22:43,941 --> 01:22:46,341
He's my business partner for years.
What do you want?

1301
01:22:46,410 --> 01:22:47,399
I want you to come home.

1302
01:22:47,478 --> 01:22:49,878
- It's what I want.
- You gotta give me more time.

1303
01:22:49,947 --> 01:22:53,542
- It's just so sad, Charlie.
- I know.

1304
01:22:53,617 --> 01:22:55,949
Get help. Help me.

1305
01:22:57,888 --> 01:23:00,755
- It's a paper plate with paint on it.
- It's a Lichtenstein.

1306
01:23:00,858 --> 01:23:02,291
It makes me dizzy.

1307
01:23:02,359 --> 01:23:04,190
Tony, Stuart's a mess.

1308
01:23:04,261 --> 01:23:07,162
He's been drinking non-stop
since he got here.

1309
01:23:07,231 --> 01:23:09,222
I'll see if Tim can drive him home.

1310
01:23:09,300 --> 01:23:13,259
- You've got to get everybody out of here.
- All right. Excuse me.

1311
01:23:13,604 --> 01:23:16,198
Know the phone number for Yellow Cab?

1312
01:23:16,273 --> 01:23:18,366
I'll take you to the airport.

1313
01:23:18,442 --> 01:23:20,876
- No, that's okay.
- No, I'd like to.

1314
01:23:20,978 --> 01:23:24,072
I can't stand the idea
of you being in a cab all by yourself.

1315
01:23:24,148 --> 01:23:26,241
Thanks. You're such a doll.

1316
01:23:26,350 --> 01:23:29,478
Every cloud has a silver lining,
even a storm cloud.

1317
01:23:36,527 --> 01:23:37,994
Is he coming?

1318
01:23:38,195 --> 01:23:39,219
No.

1319
01:23:39,296 --> 01:23:41,389
You'll tell me if he comes?

1320
01:23:43,501 --> 01:23:44,991
Metaxa, right?

1321
01:23:46,704 --> 01:23:47,898
Thanks.

1322
01:23:50,140 --> 01:23:51,869
What's the picture?

1323
01:23:53,377 --> 01:23:56,540
It's a picture of Nikko and Daphne
when they were kids.

1324
01:23:56,981 --> 01:23:59,074
Is there anything that I can do?

1325
01:23:59,149 --> 01:24:00,776
No, Nikko left...

1326
01:24:02,386 --> 01:24:04,911
written instructions for afterwards.

1327
01:24:05,489 --> 01:24:08,117
He has a prepaid work order...

1328
01:24:09,860 --> 01:24:11,760
for the Neptune Society.

1329
01:24:12,363 --> 01:24:14,388
Is there going to be a funeral?

1330
01:24:14,465 --> 01:24:17,366
No funeral, no services.

1331
01:24:18,636 --> 01:24:20,433
That's what he wants.

1332
01:24:21,338 --> 01:24:24,967
He wants me
to scatter his ashes in Santorini.

1333
01:24:27,678 --> 01:24:29,441
That's where we met.

1334
01:24:35,085 --> 01:24:36,279
I know.

1335
01:24:39,857 --> 01:24:41,484
Tony said that...

1336
01:24:42,459 --> 01:24:45,451
everyone has to leave, except for the family.

1337
01:24:46,997 --> 01:24:49,522
I wanted to ask you if I could stay.

1338
01:24:52,570 --> 01:24:55,562
When you came back,
it meant a lot to Nikko.

1339
01:24:56,340 --> 01:24:57,534
It did?

1340
01:24:58,475 --> 01:25:00,443
He didn't say so...

1341
01:25:00,811 --> 01:25:03,211
but I know he would want you to stay.

1342
01:25:03,714 --> 01:25:05,045
Thank you.

1343
01:25:08,819 --> 01:25:10,047
Douglas?

1344
01:25:10,621 --> 01:25:12,282
- Uncle Paul?
- Yeah.

1345
01:25:12,690 --> 01:25:14,487
It's good to see you.

1346
01:25:14,825 --> 01:25:16,292
It's been a...

1347
01:25:26,003 --> 01:25:27,868
You gave up your trip?

1348
01:25:27,972 --> 01:25:29,030
Yes.

1349
01:25:30,541 --> 01:25:31,803
Listen...

1350
01:25:32,576 --> 01:25:34,237
I may have gone...

1351
01:25:34,678 --> 01:25:36,475
overboard last night.

1352
01:25:37,014 --> 01:25:38,276
May have?

1353
01:25:43,721 --> 01:25:46,281
"God always has another custard pie
up his sleeve."

1354
01:25:46,357 --> 01:25:47,756
Georgy Girl.

1355
01:25:50,594 --> 01:25:52,960
My plane leaves in about an hour.

1356
01:25:53,030 --> 01:25:55,089
The family's going to have dinner.

1357
01:25:55,165 --> 01:25:56,655
"Not moussaka again."

1358
01:25:56,734 --> 01:25:58,725
Melina Mercouri in Never on Sunday.

1359
01:25:58,802 --> 01:26:00,861
Do I have something for you.

1360
01:26:00,938 --> 01:26:04,635
- The ultimate LA bad-taste jacket.
- You made fun of me when I bought it.

1361
01:26:04,708 --> 01:26:06,232
Now it's yours.

1362
01:26:06,443 --> 01:26:08,673
Wear it with enthusiasm, Matt.

1363
01:26:16,687 --> 01:26:19,315
- I love you.
- I love you, too, babe.

1364
01:26:21,358 --> 01:26:22,825
Promise me...

1365
01:26:22,893 --> 01:26:25,953
you'll make the choices
that'll make you happy.

1366
01:26:27,898 --> 01:26:29,229
I promise.

1367
01:26:41,211 --> 01:26:42,303
Remember...

1368
01:26:42,379 --> 01:26:44,609
if you need anything though...

1369
01:26:45,382 --> 01:26:46,474
call.

1370
01:26:47,751 --> 01:26:50,083
I mean, not me. I won't be here.

1371
01:26:54,525 --> 01:26:56,618
Funny to the end, aren't I?

1372
01:27:01,198 --> 01:27:03,325
You think we could change the music?

1373
01:27:03,400 --> 01:27:05,265
Why? You don't like it?

1374
01:27:05,335 --> 01:27:07,963
It's been playing over and over.

1375
01:27:08,372 --> 01:27:12,103
If you don't change it,
I am going to break that CD in half.

1376
01:27:12,209 --> 01:27:13,574
You know...

1377
01:27:14,078 --> 01:27:16,706
I always hated mushy music, but now...

1378
01:27:16,880 --> 01:27:18,541
I kind of like it.

1379
01:27:24,555 --> 01:27:25,715
"Tears?

1380
01:27:25,856 --> 01:27:29,189
"When you have been bathed
in scented wine...

1381
01:27:29,259 --> 01:27:32,319
- "your limbs caressed by sweet oils..."
- Give it a rest.

1382
01:27:32,396 --> 01:27:34,591
"When your hair's...

1383
01:27:34,732 --> 01:27:37,565
- "been combed with sandalwood."
- "My hair."

1384
01:27:38,035 --> 01:27:39,024
You mean, my hair?

1385
01:27:39,103 --> 01:27:41,765
"There will be no time for tears."

1386
01:27:42,206 --> 01:27:45,801
The Ten Commandments,
or a Vidal Sassoon commercial.

1387
01:27:47,244 --> 01:27:50,805
Will you call me tomorrow
and tell me if he went through with it?

1388
01:27:50,881 --> 01:27:52,246
Yeah, sure.

1389
01:27:52,516 --> 01:27:54,313
Did you say goodbye?

1390
01:27:56,253 --> 01:27:57,481
I can't.

1391
01:28:07,664 --> 01:28:09,859
- Here, Monty's leaving.
- Okay.

1392
01:28:10,067 --> 01:28:11,295
Babe...

1393
01:28:11,535 --> 01:28:14,470
I'd love to stay,
but I gotta go home and sort my socks.

1394
01:28:14,538 --> 01:28:16,130
This is for you.

1395
01:28:17,441 --> 01:28:20,899
- For good luck?
- You always wanted me to give you head.

1396
01:28:22,379 --> 01:28:24,472
Come on, I'll walk you out.

1397
01:28:28,085 --> 01:28:29,109
So...

1398
01:28:29,186 --> 01:28:32,622
just don't do us any favors and sing
"I Did It My Way."

1399
01:28:33,423 --> 01:28:34,651
I won't.

1400
01:28:37,094 --> 01:28:40,257
I got drunk last night,
and I was really mean to Brandon.

1401
01:28:41,365 --> 01:28:43,697
It's in your nature. He'll live.

1402
01:28:45,002 --> 01:28:46,367
He's with Monty.

1403
01:28:46,436 --> 01:28:48,836
- You doing anything tomorrow?
- No.

1404
01:28:49,039 --> 01:28:50,404
Me, neither.

1405
01:28:55,612 --> 01:28:56,977
I really...

1406
01:28:57,347 --> 01:28:58,678
miss Jack.

1407
01:29:00,284 --> 01:29:03,048
I thought about going with you tonight.

1408
01:29:03,120 --> 01:29:04,417
Monty...

1409
01:29:04,488 --> 01:29:08,356
you've been positive for eight years,
you haven't shown a sign of a problem.

1410
01:29:08,425 --> 01:29:12,156
Even if you do get sick,
you gotta stay strong.

1411
01:29:12,229 --> 01:29:13,719
Keep fighting.

1412
01:29:14,164 --> 01:29:15,927
You could get lucky.

1413
01:29:27,978 --> 01:29:31,778
The next time we see each other,
my tan's going to be darker.

1414
01:29:33,116 --> 01:29:35,141
I'll be closer to the sun.

1415
01:29:43,160 --> 01:29:45,128
Pastitsio is ready.

1416
01:29:45,662 --> 01:29:47,789
Come on, let's go over here.

1417
01:29:49,600 --> 01:29:51,591
Eat something, Mr. Stark.

1418
01:29:55,672 --> 01:29:58,835
Time for the help to leave,
Mr. Eddie's Father.

1419
01:29:59,243 --> 01:30:01,143
- Stay for dinner.
- No.

1420
01:30:01,645 --> 01:30:04,580
It's family time.
Come outside and say goodbye to me.

1421
01:30:04,648 --> 01:30:08,448
- Okay. Sorry about my dad.
- Nikko, should I make you a plate?

1422
01:30:10,921 --> 01:30:12,912
I'll get one in a minute.

1423
01:30:17,261 --> 01:30:18,888
I feel like a stewardess.

1424
01:30:18,962 --> 01:30:20,896
"Bye-bye, so nice having you, bye.

1425
01:30:20,964 --> 01:30:23,865
"Nice having you,
bye-bye, please come back."

1426
01:30:31,341 --> 01:30:33,434
Don't you get morbid on me.

1427
01:30:34,144 --> 01:30:36,374
This won't be morbid, asshole.

1428
01:30:37,147 --> 01:30:39,638
I'll always be looking out for you.

1429
01:30:40,384 --> 01:30:44,013
Every once in a while,
just flash me that big Nikko smile.

1430
01:30:44,554 --> 01:30:45,816
Every day.

1431
01:30:49,026 --> 01:30:51,256
Do you own a pair of scissors?

1432
01:30:52,529 --> 01:30:54,360
I want you to go home right now...

1433
01:30:54,431 --> 01:30:56,729
and cut these bangs.

1434
01:30:57,601 --> 01:30:58,829
Promise?

1435
01:31:02,306 --> 01:31:04,467
You're a beautiful woman, Charlene.

1436
01:31:04,541 --> 01:31:07,977
How is Mr. Right going to find you
hiding behind this?

1437
01:31:08,178 --> 01:31:09,839
Look at that face.

1438
01:31:11,515 --> 01:31:13,380
It's a beautiful face.

1439
01:31:14,518 --> 01:31:17,510
I want you to stay off Ding Dongs.

1440
01:31:23,894 --> 01:31:25,794
I gotta go back inside.

1441
01:31:26,663 --> 01:31:27,857
I know.

1442
01:31:28,398 --> 01:31:29,660
Goodbye.

1443
01:31:43,747 --> 01:31:46,341
Houdini. Come on.

1444
01:31:48,518 --> 01:31:49,780
Lie there. That's it.

1445
01:31:49,853 --> 01:31:52,014
When I was a little girl, I was so mad...

1446
01:31:52,089 --> 01:31:54,489
when you threw out my favorite toy.

1447
01:31:54,558 --> 01:31:56,321
- How old was I?
- 10.

1448
01:31:57,527 --> 01:32:00,189
But you love me now, don't you?

1449
01:32:01,698 --> 01:32:03,962
Yes. I love you now.

1450
01:32:05,135 --> 01:32:07,000
This is special sauce.

1451
01:32:07,504 --> 01:32:08,664
The sauce is good?

1452
01:32:08,739 --> 01:32:10,331
It's from a can.

1453
01:32:23,253 --> 01:32:24,652
Really good.

1454
01:32:36,600 --> 01:32:38,090
Look, all right.

1455
01:32:38,602 --> 01:32:41,127
First off, we've got to keep him
from drinking more.

1456
01:32:41,638 --> 01:32:45,369
He's gotta keep his head clear
to say goodbye to his family.

1457
01:32:45,776 --> 01:32:49,576
What's all this yip-yapping?
And what's with these sad faces?

1458
01:32:49,913 --> 01:32:52,609
- You know, we gotta take a walk.
- Nick.

1459
01:32:52,682 --> 01:32:54,775
I'm not losing my mind yet.

1460
01:32:56,219 --> 01:32:59,552
- Nurse Ratched.
- I don't want you wandering off again.

1461
01:32:59,623 --> 01:33:00,817
I won't be long.

1462
01:33:00,891 --> 01:33:03,485
Just don't put me in this position.

1463
01:33:03,560 --> 01:33:07,121
- How long have I got after I take them?
- You've got 20 minutes.

1464
01:33:07,197 --> 01:33:08,391
Thirty, max.

1465
01:33:08,465 --> 01:33:10,660
All right. I gotta do this, Tony.

1466
01:33:10,734 --> 01:33:11,996
I got to.

1467
01:33:14,104 --> 01:33:15,594
Don't be long.

1468
01:33:19,843 --> 01:33:21,401
What's going on?

1469
01:33:21,478 --> 01:33:24,276
I don't know. Nick wants to talk to Brandon.

1470
01:33:26,049 --> 01:33:27,573
Come on, Opala.

1471
01:33:29,986 --> 01:33:31,248
Listen...

1472
01:33:31,455 --> 01:33:35,721
I want you to go back to making
the kind of films you made in college.

1473
01:33:37,060 --> 01:33:38,152
Okay.

1474
01:33:41,398 --> 01:33:44,299
You made such a difference in my life, Nick.

1475
01:33:45,068 --> 01:33:47,366
You brought me out of my shell.

1476
01:33:47,537 --> 01:33:50,438
- The years that we spent together...
- Yeah.

1477
01:33:50,874 --> 01:33:52,603
We had great times.

1478
01:33:54,578 --> 01:33:55,806
Come on.

1479
01:34:17,234 --> 01:34:20,135
Hey, Violet. Hi, honey.

1480
01:34:26,610 --> 01:34:28,737
- Mr. Stark.
- Howdy, neighbor.

1481
01:34:29,679 --> 01:34:32,273
I see him every day,
and I can't remember his name.

1482
01:34:32,349 --> 01:34:34,840
I am going out of town. Can you feed them?

1483
01:34:34,918 --> 01:34:36,010
Sure.

1484
01:34:36,386 --> 01:34:39,480
Actually, my friend here can feed them.
Brandon.

1485
01:34:39,556 --> 01:34:41,148
Good. Thank you.

1486
01:34:42,025 --> 01:34:44,357
They've been here all this time.

1487
01:34:44,461 --> 01:34:46,429
I need you to be strong for me.

1488
01:34:46,496 --> 01:34:48,464
I don't want you crying.

1489
01:34:51,301 --> 01:34:52,666
You know...

1490
01:34:53,336 --> 01:34:54,667
I can barely see.

1491
01:34:54,738 --> 01:34:57,798
It's like looking down a long tube,
what I see.

1492
01:35:02,479 --> 01:35:04,606
Come on, I'll take you back.

1493
01:35:04,948 --> 01:35:06,415
Bye-bye, Violet.

1494
01:35:08,552 --> 01:35:10,349
Would you take Opala?

1495
01:35:10,854 --> 01:35:14,381
You can't let her loose in the house,
or she'll rip everything to shit.

1496
01:35:14,457 --> 01:35:18,154
She gets one cup of dry food in the morning
and one cup at night.

1497
01:35:18,228 --> 01:35:21,686
Her name's Hawaiian for "trash."
Brandon found her in...

1498
01:35:33,710 --> 01:35:37,168
I told him to make sure
that he got a hold of everything...

1499
01:35:37,247 --> 01:35:39,340
that I told him he needed...

1500
01:35:39,416 --> 01:35:42,010
because I have to keep some distance.

1501
01:35:44,955 --> 01:35:45,979
Hi.

1502
01:36:16,586 --> 01:36:19,111
Can't a guy take a leak around here?

1503
01:36:20,390 --> 01:36:21,550
Sorry.

1504
01:36:25,962 --> 01:36:27,862
God, that was the best.

1505
01:36:28,198 --> 01:36:30,758
That was the Christmas
we spent in Switzerland.

1506
01:36:30,834 --> 01:36:33,598
And then New Year's Eve in St. Moritz.

1507
01:36:33,937 --> 01:36:37,771
We took the chair lift up the mountain,
and skied down to the Niarchos party.

1508
01:36:37,841 --> 01:36:39,468
We were like James Bond.

1509
01:36:39,542 --> 01:36:42,511
We step out of our ski suits,
and had black tie on underneath.

1510
01:36:42,579 --> 01:36:44,171
Inside this mansion...

1511
01:36:44,247 --> 01:36:48,308
were all these rich 20-year-olds,
lying around, passed out.

1512
01:36:48,385 --> 01:36:52,287
And this huge vat of caviar,
with cigarette butts put out in it.

1513
01:36:57,227 --> 01:36:59,718
Dad sure is taking this well.

1514
01:37:05,435 --> 01:37:07,596
Which reminds me,
when I was 16 years old...

1515
01:37:07,671 --> 01:37:10,765
Dad takes Daphne and me
on a camping trip in January.

1516
01:37:11,107 --> 01:37:12,699
The ground is frozen solid.

1517
01:37:12,776 --> 01:37:16,177
Tony always gave me a hard time
about the Winnebago.

1518
01:37:16,246 --> 01:37:18,214
He called it "Cleopatra's Barge."

1519
01:37:18,548 --> 01:37:19,879
Excuse me.

1520
01:37:22,819 --> 01:37:24,719
I'm going to do a line.

1521
01:38:20,877 --> 01:38:22,276
That's that.

1522
01:38:56,646 --> 01:38:58,511
We were good together.

1523
01:39:04,187 --> 01:39:06,417
I'm going to miss you so much.

1524
01:39:08,091 --> 01:39:09,888
You'll find somebody.

1525
01:39:11,060 --> 01:39:12,721
I want you.

1526
01:39:13,830 --> 01:39:15,627
I'll still be around.

1527
01:39:17,634 --> 01:39:19,829
You always said you were an atheist.

1528
01:39:19,903 --> 01:39:23,361
Agnostic.
That just means I haven't had proof yet.

1529
01:39:24,908 --> 01:39:27,809
But I have a strong feeling I'm not leaving.

1530
01:39:29,979 --> 01:39:32,470
Will you send me some kind of sign?

1531
01:39:34,884 --> 01:39:35,942
Yes.

1532
01:40:19,062 --> 01:40:20,996
- We're close.
- How close?

1533
01:40:21,064 --> 01:40:23,362
Pretty close. He already took the pills.

1534
01:40:23,433 --> 01:40:25,162
Thanks for staying.

1535
01:40:30,073 --> 01:40:31,472
Your mother needs you.

1536
01:40:58,735 --> 01:41:00,600
Need anything, Amalia?

1537
01:41:01,271 --> 01:41:04,069
No, thank you very much. I'm fine.

1538
01:41:21,691 --> 01:41:22,919
Come on.

1539
01:41:26,796 --> 01:41:28,286
Sit on my lap.

1540
01:41:34,571 --> 01:41:37,062
I want you to promise me one thing.

1541
01:41:39,275 --> 01:41:40,606
Promise...

1542
01:41:41,177 --> 01:41:43,042
you will stop smoking.

1543
01:41:47,350 --> 01:41:48,578
I can't.

1544
01:41:51,621 --> 01:41:52,713
Okay.

1545
01:41:54,290 --> 01:41:57,259
Then promise me you won't wear black.

1546
01:41:59,729 --> 01:42:00,821
Okay.

1547
01:42:03,733 --> 01:42:05,394
Always remember...

1548
01:42:06,169 --> 01:42:07,898
I took care of you.

1549
01:42:09,639 --> 01:42:10,867
You did.

1550
01:42:14,510 --> 01:42:15,602
Nick.

1551
01:42:16,512 --> 01:42:19,242
Come here, I want to show you something.

1552
01:42:26,756 --> 01:42:28,849
Come on. Come sit over here.

1553
01:42:31,794 --> 01:42:33,284
This is our...

1554
01:42:34,297 --> 01:42:36,288
trip to Europe last year.

1555
01:42:38,735 --> 01:42:41,169
This is you arriving in Amsterdam.

1556
01:42:41,471 --> 01:42:42,768
Check out your eyes.

1557
01:42:42,839 --> 01:42:45,672
- Not a pretty sight.
- Not a pretty sight.

1558
01:42:51,514 --> 01:42:53,539
See, this is the next day.

1559
01:42:56,552 --> 01:42:58,645
Can I talk to you a minute?

1560
01:42:59,022 --> 01:43:00,353
Excuse me.

1561
01:43:03,526 --> 01:43:06,927
Shouldn't he be spending these moments
with his family?

1562
01:43:08,331 --> 01:43:11,266
I don't want him to nod off in front of them.

1563
01:43:13,102 --> 01:43:15,696
We have to get him into his bed soon.

1564
01:43:21,044 --> 01:43:22,136
Okay.

1565
01:43:23,946 --> 01:43:25,436
Remember this?

1566
01:43:25,581 --> 01:43:29,415
It's a train station
where we dropped off your French friends.

1567
01:43:31,187 --> 01:43:32,848
Where are my keys?

1568
01:43:36,225 --> 01:43:38,216
You don't need your keys.

1569
01:43:48,571 --> 01:43:50,300
Remember the view from our room?

1570
01:43:51,607 --> 01:43:54,132
It's time for us to leave, you guys.

1571
01:43:55,745 --> 01:43:57,269
He's starting to go.

1572
01:43:58,247 --> 01:43:59,236
Mother...

1573
01:44:02,385 --> 01:44:03,909
I love art.

1574
01:44:09,425 --> 01:44:11,620
This is us back at the hotel.

1575
01:44:33,282 --> 01:44:35,477
It's okay, Nick.

1576
01:44:43,192 --> 01:44:44,682
I'm so sleepy.

1577
01:45:04,347 --> 01:45:05,678
This is it.

1578
01:45:05,748 --> 01:45:07,682
Don't be scared, Nikko.

1579
01:45:07,750 --> 01:45:09,377
It's me, Brandon.

1580
01:45:11,454 --> 01:45:14,423
- This is it.
- Just lie back and relax.

1581
01:45:15,424 --> 01:45:18,416
That's it. Just think about...

1582
01:45:18,861 --> 01:45:21,989
us going up the chair lift together.

1583
01:45:24,267 --> 01:45:26,201
That sun feels warm.

1584
01:45:27,036 --> 01:45:30,335
And with that icy wind
blowing on your face...

1585
01:45:30,773 --> 01:45:33,071
it's a weird feeling, isn't it?

1586
01:45:34,076 --> 01:45:36,806
We're almost at the top of the mountain.

1587
01:45:37,346 --> 01:45:39,439
We're gliding off the lift.

1588
01:45:39,982 --> 01:45:42,177
We're stopping up at the top.

1589
01:45:43,319 --> 01:45:45,412
Now we're pushing off.

1590
01:45:47,223 --> 01:45:48,884
We're flying down.

1591
01:45:50,626 --> 01:45:52,719
Ski with me, through powder.

